						               													<description>The main principle of this game is a generally known law of magnetism, saying that charged particles of the same signs repel each other and attract the opposite, in other words: plus attracts minus, minus attracts plus, plus repels plus and minus repels minus. Players, using this principle, perform actions with their pawns, aiming to place five of them in a row. The first to achieve this goal wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has 45 two-sided pawns with a plus sign and a minus on the other side.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player in his/her turn must perform: &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     place his pawn from the pool on the board &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;and (if possible) &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     make one additional action out of the following: &amp;#10;         repelling the pawn on the board &amp;#10;         attracting the pawn on the board &amp;#10;    &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;and (if the additional action gives such an effect) &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     a pawn's reaction after an additional action (or a sequence of pawns' reactions)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
